Download the bot's code to your VPS:git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/ai-agent-trader-blueprint.git
Go into the bot's folder: cd ai-agent-trader-blueprint
Create the .env file from the template:cp .env.example .env
Edit the .env file to add your keys:nano .env (Enter all your API keys and the base64 private key you got in Step 3.
Press Ctrl+X, then Y, and finally Enter to save the file)
Install Python Dependencies: pip3 install -r requirements.txt
Run the Bot:screen -S mybot
Now, run the bot inside the screen session:python3 bot_blueprint.py(Once the bot starts running, detach from the screen session (the bot will continue to run in the background):
Press Ctrl+A and then press D)
Check the Bot's Status (Dashboard Check):screen -ls(You should see a session named mybot)
To re-attach to the screen and see the bot's live logs:screen -r mybot(You can now see all the bot's activity. To detach again, press Ctrl+A then D)
Stop the Bot:FirsTo stop the bot press:screen -r mybot
To stop the bot, press:Ctrl+C
To completely close the screen session:exit
